		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Right in the introduction:<br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">The tiles are stored in a ROM chip on the game cartridge<br /></div><br /><br />24% of all NES games used CHR RAM instead of ROM.<br /><br />Also, not all the bits exist for the 4 bytes of data in sprite ram, but that's just an unimportant nitpicky detail.  The bits that do nothing can't even be read back.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
