	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Also, it seems like you were struggling on the attribute tables.<br />Divide up a byte into bits like ddccbbaa, and the bits apply to the four 16x16 sections of a 32x32 region like this:<br />AB<br />CD<br />aa means it's a 2-bit value (0-3) that determines which palette goes into A, aa is the lowest two bits of the byte.  Then bb is another two-bit value, etc.<br /><br />Attribute tables are 8 bytes wide and 8 bytes tall, and take up the last 64 bytes of a nametable, instead of having two more rows of tiles.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


